===Talking to Ribs===
* '''Ribs:''' Ahoy, young whippersnapper. Have you come to hear a tale from old Ribs?
* '''Player:''' Kind of, I guess. I was hoping you could tell me about Will and Anne, along with the map they stole.
* '''Ribs:''' A dark day. A very dark day. Those young fools know not what they have wrought upon themselves.
* '''Player:''' That being?
* '''Ribs:''' A curse! A curse most foul! That map marked the resting place of the Crimson Kraken! She was a deadly vessel, captained by none other than Barnacle Barnaby himself!
* '''Player:''' Barnacle Barnaby? Who's that then?
* '''Ribs:''' You have not heard the tale of Barnacle Barnaby? You have not heard of the scourge of the Unquiet Ocean?
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|No, tell me about him.}}
** '''Player:''' No, tell me about him.
** '''Ribs:''' He was a cruel and vicious pirate. Orchestrator of the Driftwood Massacre and unleasher of the Plague of Black Mists. He believed himself untouchable, but his arrogance was his undoing.
** '''Ribs:''' Despite the warnings of many, Barnacle Barnaby attempted to plunder the Skullhorde, but his only reward was a deadly curse. It destroyed the Crimson Kraken, condemning all on board to a watery grave.
** '''Player:''' And you had a map leading to the wreck of the Kraken?
** '''Ribs:''' Aye! I purchased the map from Ulrich the Unfortunate, the sole survivor of the Kraken, but I had no intention of using it. I knew that no good would ever come from seeking the Kraken.
** '''Player:''' Then why not destroy the map?
** '''Ribs:''' And risk the wrath of Barnaby's ghost? No. Better the map be locked away, so that neither it nor the curse could harm anyone else.
** '''Player:''' I'm not sure I quite follow your reasoning for keeping it, but I guess it doesn't matter now. I'm afraid Will and Anne found and looted the Kraken.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|Now's not really the time for tales.}}
** '''Player:''' Now's not really the time for tales.
** '''Ribs:''' You are a fool for thinking that way, but on your head be it. The short of it is that Barnaby and the Kraken were cursed, condemning him and his crew to a watery grave.
** '''Player:''' I see. Well, I'm afraid Will and Anne found and looted the Kraken.
** {{tact|continues}}
* '''Ribs:''' I feared as much, though part of me still hoped it would not come to be. Tell me, did they find Barnaby's medallion?
* '''Player:''' They did. It was actually the only thing they were interested in.
* '''Ribs:''' Then the foul curse is now free once more. They must be stopped!
* '''Player:''' Well, I do have my own personal reasons for wanting Will and Anne dealt with. Maybe I could try and find them.
* '''Ribs:''' You are a brave soul indeed, but that is just what is needed at a time like this.
* '''Ribs:''' You should talk to Steve. He already put out a bounty for Will and Anne after the theft. He might have heard something about where they could have gone.
* {{tact|end}}

